{{Year box}} '''1791 in sports''' describes the year's events in world sport.
==[[Baseball]]== '''Earliest known reference''' * The [[Pittsfield, Massachusetts#Baseball in Pittsfield|broken window by-law]] in [[Pittsfield, Massachusetts]] prohibited "baseball" and other ball games within 80 yards of the new meeting house, the earliest known reference to "baseball" in North America.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pittsfieldlibrary.org/baseball.html |title=Pittsfield's 1791 Baseball Bylaw |date=August 2006 |publisher=Pittsfield Library |accessdate=2011-08-15}}</ref>
==[[Boxing]]== '''Events''' * 17 January — [[Benjamin Brain|"Big Ben" Brain]] defeated [[Tom Johnson (bareknuckle boxer)|Tom Johnson]] at [[Wrotham]] in the 18th round of a fight lasting 21 minutes to claim the Championship of England. Brain held the title until his death from [[cirrhosis of the liver]] in 1794.<ref>[http://www.cyberboxingzone.com/boxing/brain-benjamin.htm Cyber Boxing Zone – Ben Brain]. Retrieved on 6 November 2009.</ref>
